rComments: He has lots of trouble communicating the basics.

Sure he is more philosophical in his approach but that is not necessarily bad. His exams are REALLY fair. He'll always clarify when you ask him too. Because his approach is more philosophical, it's even more important to do your readings before class; because then you can follow and understand what inferences he is making.
If you can avoid him, do it. Extremely hard to follow. Although he is clearly passionate, he not a good professor... teaching is not for him.

Son cours était très intéressant mais pas toujours facile à suivre. Le professeur Sérafin est passionné par la matière et l'aborde de matière plus académique/philosophique que pratique, ce qui amène à des réflexions plus approfondies mais implique un peu plus de travail à côté pour trier les informations, surtout en vue de l'examen.

Doesn't teach Canadian precedent which makes it hard to actually apply concepts in practice . Very hard to decipher what is important when he talks, and especially what is his opinion or something endorsed by the courts. Very philosophical in his method which is quite different than regular courses and can be hard to follow
